    <section id="accessibility">
      <h2>Accessibility Best Practices</h2>
      <p>Accessibility ensures that your website can be used by people with disabilities. Use semantic tags like <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;main&gt;</code>, and <code>&lt;footer&gt;</code>, and provide alternative navigation options.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use meaningful landmarks and roles.</li>
        <li>Use <code>alt</code> attributes for images (not shown here).</li>
        <li>Label navigation and sections clearly.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="seo">
      <h2>Basic SEO Techniques</h2>
      <p>Search Engine Optimization helps your content appear in search results. Structure and clarity are key.</p>
      <h3>Tips for Better SEO</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Use descriptive titles and headings.</li>
        <li>Include keywords in a natural way.</li>
        <li>Use meta tags for description and keywords.</li>
        <li>Keep your content relevant and readable.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
